إِنَّا نَحْنُ نُحْىِ ٱلْمَوْتَىٰ وَنَكْتُبُ مَا قَدَّمُوا۟ وَءَاثَـٰرَهُمْ ۚ وَكُلَّ شَىْءٍ 
(36:12) أَحْصَيْنَـٰهُ فِىٓ إِمَامٍۢ مُّبِينٍۢ 

13
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:40,460
We praise God, and we bear witness that there is no god except the one God.

14
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:46,840
And we declare that all devotion and all worship is directed to God alone.

15
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:56,760
SURA 39
أَلَا لِلَّهِ ٱلدِّينُ ٱلْخَالِصُ
devotion and worship belong to God alone.

16
00:02:56,760 --> 00:03:14,120
Some of you probably saw this bombshell where there is announcement

17
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:20,100
that I have been commissioned a messenger of God.

18
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:30,080
And this is probably the most difficult announcement that I have ever come up with.

19
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:43,460
But something that I have known since 1980. And you can see that I was, I was coward.

20
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:50,160
I was afraid to come up with it. I dreaded the time when I may have to announce it.

21
00:03:50,160 --> 00:04:00,544
Because there is a general tendency to resent anybody saying - I am going to use a wrong statement now,

22
00:04:00,544 --> 00:04:08,720
but this is what the resentment is for. Generally, people resent somebody saying "I'm better than you"

23
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:14,588
or what appears to be saying "I am better than you."

24
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:29,460
And even the Quran condemns such a statement, in SURA 4, God says "note those who exalt themselves.

25
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:36,540
God is the one who exalts whomever He wills without the least injustice."

26
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:48,100
The resentment in this case results from two things: ignorance and idol-worship.

27
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:55,940
Ignorance, because the Quran teaches us that a messenger of God

28
00:04:55,940 --> 00:05:01,960
is not necessarily better than anyone else in the congregation.

29
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:12,060
In SURA 18, from verses 60 to verse 82, we see that God picked out one of the biggest messengers,

30
00:05:12,060 --> 00:05:22,080
Moses, one that God said "I made you for myself."
 (20:41) وَٱصْطَنَعْتُكَ لِنَفْسِى
"I made you for Me."

31
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:30,040
And in other place, God said
(20:39) لِتُصْنَعَ عَلَىٰ عَيْنِىٓ
"I had you made before My eyes."

32
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:39,680
And we see in those verses that God sent Moses to "one of our servants, whom we bestowed,

33
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,300
we gave mercy and knowledge."

34
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:45,080
And Moses proved to be a lousy student.

35
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:51,580
So, this teaches us that a messenger of God is not necessarily better than

36
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:56,800
anyone else in the congregation.

37
00:05:56,800 --> 00:06:04,080
I can think of quite a few of you whom I consider better than me.

38
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:11,900
I see people, when I was their age, I used to go to the Saints and ask for help.

39
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:15,660
I was an idol worshiper, when I was that age.

40
00:06:15,660 --> 00:06:23,600
Yet here they are, a lot younger. They have 20-year head start, compared to me. And so

41
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:27,908
This is the first thing. Ignorance causes this resentment.

42
00:06:27,908 --> 00:06:36,436
Idol worship because the people idolize the messenger of God and they made him next to God.

43
00:06:36,436 --> 00:06:41,320
They made him a god besides God. So, when you mention the word "messenger of God",

44
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:44,260
they are awed, you know.

45
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:50,820
But the truth is, a messenger of God is - the Quran repeats "a human being like you."

46
00:06:50,820 --> 00:07:02,960
or in colloquial, local terms a flopster like the rest of us whom we can kid around and who can be silly.

47
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:15,140
What is more the Quran teaches that a messenger of God... if a person is picked out as a messenger of God, a commissioned messenger of God....there are kinds of messengers

48
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:17,618
does not even guarantee Heaven.

49
00:07:17,618 --> 00:07:23,123
And we see this in SURAH 39 verse 65

50
00:07:23,123 --> 00:07:31,580
where it says "it has been revealed to you and to those before you that if you ever fall in idolatry,

51
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:37,680
all you work will be nullified and you will be among the losers.

52
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:42,060
So, a messenger of God does not even guarantee heaven.

53
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:49,700
And this is why we see in SURA 21, verse 28 that the messengers are worried about their own neck.

54
00:07:49,740 --> 00:07:57,760
We are all familiar with these verses. But the people who have either ignorance or idolatry in them,

55
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:02,540
they resent an announcement like this.

56
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:16,440
If a person is picked as a messenger of God, it's a difficult job. It's a very difficult job.

57
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:29,580
There is no material gain out of it. I certainly will not allow a single penny to enter my personal pocket because of this or because of religious reasons.

58
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:37,660
I'm not a professional religionist and I will not allow a penny to enter my pocket from religious activities

59
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:39,920
Because then the motive changes.

60
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:47,140
And the Quran repeats "stay with those who do not ask you for wages."

61
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:57,760
The Quran says in SURA 49... Quran gives us the criteria of who is better than whom. 

62
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,963
And in says in Arabic

63
00:08:58,963 --> 00:09:00,551
(49:13) إِنَّ أَكْرَمَكُمْ عِندَ ٱللَّهِ أَتْقَىٰكُمْ 

64
00:09:00,551 --> 00:09:03,628
The best among you is the most righteous.

65
00:09:03,628 --> 00:09:10,360
It didn't say the best among you is the messenger of God, or the richest, or the tallest,

66
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:13,320
or the most knowledgeable.

67
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:18,040
"The best among you is the most righteous."

68
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:24,060
So, all these things will teach us that messenger of God is no big deal.

69
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:31,400
It is just a vehicle that God uses to communicate with us.

70
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:35,240
A center of information.

71
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:47,260
And with it goes a difficult job, a very difficult job, the abuse, the slandering, the threats.

72
00:09:47,360 --> 00:10:01,700
And God says....I believe it's in 42:51. Yes. In SURA 42, verse 51, God says that

73
00:10:01,740 --> 00:10:07,580
"No human being can communicate with God, except through three ways:

74
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:13,020
inspiration, or from behind a barrier, or through a messenger"

75
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:17,460
that through whom God spreads certain information.

76
00:10:17,460 --> 00:10:22,420
So, people will know this is reliable information, that this is from God.

77
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:27,120
We are people who follow the Quran, the whole Quran and nothing but the Quran.

78
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:33,920
Therefore, anybody, and this means anybody, who brings any information must conform to the Quran.

79
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,620
The whole Quran, nothing but the Quran.

80
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:39,700
And if anyone, and underline anyone, 

81
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:46,800
comes up with any information that is not confirmed by the Quran, we tell him "forget it!"

82
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:49,260
We don't accept it.

83
00:10:49,340 --> 00:11:00,060
So, the criterion is preaching, confirming existing scripture, the Quran and nothing else.

84
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:02,660
No innovations.

85
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:12,240
Now, we come to the question: is it possible that we receive a messenger from God?

86
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:19,920
If you ask an average Muhammadan, they will tell you Muhammad was the last messenger.

87
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:29,980
But they have no basis, for saying this. And the Quran gives us a precedent since Joseph, the prophet Joseph.

88
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:33,520
When he died, the Quran teaches us that the people said "okay, that was the last messenger,

89
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:36,008
we'll never see another messenger after that.

90
00:11:36,008 --> 00:11:38,980
So, this is a human tendency.

91
00:11:38,980 --> 00:11:43,980
And the Muhammdans claim that Muhammad was the last messenger. He's not.

92
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:52,360
In SURA 33, verse 40, God says "Muhammad was not the father of any of your men. He was a messenger

93
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:55,880
of God and the final prophet."

94
00:11:55,880 --> 00:12:00,380
So, here we see a distinction between prophet and messenger.

95
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:07,640
A prophet is one who delivers a scripture, like Jesus, Moses, Muhammad. They are prophets.

96
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:14,640
And we this clearly in SURA 3, verse 81, where God says that He made a covenant with the prophets

97
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:18,100
that He will give them the scripture and wisdom."

98
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:21,240
So, here we have the definition of a prophet.

99
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:27,880
Then, God made a covenant with us, with you and me, with every human being. He said "then,

100
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:33,140
when a messenger comes to you, confirming existing scripture.

101
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:38,200
So, there's the definition of a messenger. "When a messenger comes to you confirming

102
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:43,840
existing scripture, you shall believe in him and support him."

103
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:48,180
God said "do you make a pledge with me?"

104
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:49,740
And we all said "yes, we do."

105
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:59,000
And God said "you have thus borne witness and I bear witness along with you."

106
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:03,800
Therefore, it is possible that there will be messengers after Muhammad.

107
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:12,000
In SURA 7, verse 35, it says "o children of Adam, when messengers come to you, reciting

108
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:22,880
My revelations to you, those of you who believe are the successful ones." This is SURA 7, verse 35.

109
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:29,480
Obviously, it is for people after the Quran. As a matter of fact, the verse begins by saying "o children of Adam."

110
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:38,020
So, as long as there are children of Adam on this Earth, this verse is valid.

111
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:41,720
If messengers are coming after Muhammad, what do they look like?

112
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:46,200
What will a messenger look like after Muhammad?

113
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:50,300
Just think of any human being. What are his characteristics? You think he'll be walking on water

114
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:55,000
or walking on the air or coming with 3 angels on each side or something.

115
00:13:55,000 --> 00:14:01,300
He's just one of us, just a human being.

116
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:10,320
Some people came. I wanna answer the question why, why send a messenger?

117
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,800
Why does God send a messenger?

118
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:23,640
Why not just go the same way that people have been going? Reading the Quran, following the Quran.

119
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:30,980
Well, one important element is the test. Because of this covenant that we made with God.

120
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:37,040
What are you going to do if a messenger of God comes and says "worship God alone,

121
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:43,240
and forget about the human beings; Muhammad, Jesus, Moses or anybody.

122
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:48,700
You must devote yourself totally to God alone."

123
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:53,960
One who will preach the Quran, God's proven scripture.

124
00:14:53,960 --> 00:15:00,500
What are you going to do? Are you gonna scoff at him? Are you gonna help him, morally?

125
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:03,480
Are you gonna rally around him?

126
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:06,640
What are you going to do?
A test.

127
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:10,080
Another test is the test of ego.

128
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:16,760
The Quran repeats they said "Oh, he just wants to be better than we are. He wants to be a leader."

129
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:22,360
And this is emphasized throughout the Quran.

130
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:30,660
You're gonna find some verses in here.
And there is in SURA 17, verse 94, it says "what

131
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:36,700
prevented many people from believing was that they said "you mean God sent a human being

132
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:41,340
to be a messenger?""

133
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:52,780
And in SURA 64, verses 5 &amp; 6, I'm gonna read them for you.

134
00:15:52,780 --> 00:15:58,220
"Did you not receive the news of those who disbelieved in the past?

135
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:04,920
They suffered the consequences of their decision and deserved painful retribution. Why?

136
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:11,440
This is because their messengers went to them with clear revelations, but they said "human beings

137
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:13,920
to guide us?"

138
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:20,360
Thus, they disbelieved and turned away. God does not need them.

139
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:31,340
So, it's a tremendous test to accept somebody who says he is a messenger of God.

140
00:16:31,340 --> 00:16:35,000
There's an ego here. We're required to kill the ego.

141
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:40,680
And this applies to all of us.
One of the requirements in the Quran.

142
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:47,420
The egotistic person will resent anything like this and will be deprived.

143
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:53,840
And God says in the Quran "I will divert from my revelations those who are arrogant."

144
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:57,653
(7:146) سَأَصْرِفُ عَنْ ءَايَـٰتِىَ ٱلَّذِينَ يَتَكَبَّرُونَ فِى ٱلْأَرْض 

145
00:16:57,653 --> 00:17:00,980
I will send them away. God will actively send them away.

146
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:05,840
So, this is something we have to kill, the ego.

147
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:19,840
So, many people came and said they were messengers of God. Baháʼu'lláh was one of them. And Ghulam Ahmad of Pakistan said he was a messenger of God. 

148
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:25,440
And Joseph Smith, the Mormon leader, said he was a messenger of God.

149
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:36,800
But God made it mandatory that a messenger comes with proof, certain signs.

150
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:41,300
Moses brought all kinds of proofs.
Saleh brought proofs.

151
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:49,160
Jesus came with signs that he is authorized and sent by God.

152
00:17:49,220 --> 00:17:57,620
And on that difficult day, a few days ago, when... I'm going to give you all details.

153
00:17:57,620 --> 00:18:05,060
I'm not gonna be mysterious and say I was told this and that and leave it hanging.

154
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:10,327
I'm going to give you... everything's is gonna be wide open in front of you and I will tell you exactly what happened

155
00:18:10,327 --> 00:18:13,770
in time if the time doesn't help us now.

156
00:18:15,140 --> 00:18:27,740
But this reminds me of the fellow... you've heard this... I told some of you at least this before... but this fellow was the most curious person in town

157
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:37,420
and he would just ask questions. He'd always ask questions. And one time, he was sitting in the bar or the pub or whatever the place is

158
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:49,180
and then comes in this man with one leg and he sits next to him and this very curious person... of course, he's curious, you know... "how did you lose your leg?"

159
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:51,740
He wants to know.

160
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:56,780
And the man with one leg knows that he is the most curious person in town.

161
00:18:56,780 --> 00:19:01,620
He would just die to know, how did this fellow lose his leg?

162
00:19:01,620 --> 00:19:12,080
So, he told... the man with the one leg told him, the curious fellow.... told the curious fellow. "I will tell you on one condition."

163
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:18,040
And he said "anything... anything... just tell me... anything.... just tell me what to do and I will do it. Just tell me... anything."

164
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:22,560
He said "you ask only one question and you don't ask any questions after that." 

165
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:26,160
He said "OK. OK. I do it. Just tell me. How did you lose your leg?"

166
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:30,040
He said "it was bitten."

167
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:35,820
So, I'm sure that curious guy died on the spot because he couldn't ask any more questions. 

168
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:41,280
So I'm not going to be mysterious with you, I'm gonna tell you everything gradually.

169
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:53,440
But on that difficult day, when I realized that I must announce. I mean, I chickened out for 8 years, now.

170
00:19:56,380 --> 00:20:07,420
I needed some signs and I was shown. I had some signs but I was shown a couple of additional signs on that day.

171
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:16,220
Now, I will share with you some of the signs that will assure all of us.

172
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:27,113
Now, the first sign, of course, is the mathematical miracle of the Quran which is very simple and people should have seen it in the last 1400 years. 

173
00:20:27,113 --> 00:20:38,740
Literally, thousands of scholars looked in the Quran and counted all its words, its letters, its vowels - those signs, little signs. They counted everything in the Quran.

174
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:44,420
But they never came up with the mathematical composition of the Quran.

175
00:20:44,420 --> 00:20:51,540
BISMI ALLAH, 19 letters. The number of SURAs 19 times 6. The first revelation, 19 words. The last revelation, 19 words.

176
00:20:51,540 --> 00:20:56,300
All these are simple things that they should have discovered.

177
00:20:56,300 --> 00:21:00,920
But God reserved this for a person called Rashad, as we see

178
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:05,200
in the index of the Quran page 320

179
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:11,220
which was printed one year before I was born,

180
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:21,260
that index. It's a comprehensive index. And on page 320, you'll see that the root word RASHADA is mentioned 19 times. 

